  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Mongolian Single Moms Escape Trash Salvaging</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will setup of a charity shop and train 6 single mothers and 1 person with disabilities so they can earn a sustainable income to support their families. This will allow them and their children to stop salvaging trash. A portion of the revenue will be placed in a joint fund for the children&apos;s schooling and to provide support for 400 community members. After six months, this project will be scaled up, building additional stores, forming a cooperative and impacting 1,000 people.</narrative>
  </description>
